					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5083930#post-4201235</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5083930/scp-3417#post-4201235</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 29 Mar 2019 20:14:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, people may be noticed that I've removed the Ad Astra Per Aspera theme from this and every other AAPA tale I've written that has used it. For a while now I've become increasingly aware that the theme has been causing heavy eyestrain issues, ranging from the high contrast between the light gray and dark gray text and the blaring neon colors. I've tried to make improvements, some of which have worked, but by now I've decided that the theme (sadly) won't work out.</p> <p>Does this mean AAPA will go without a cool theme? Nope! I've started work on a completely new theme for the canon, which you can find test pages for <a href="http://topia.wikidot.com/3417-css">here</a> (applied to this SCP) and <a href="http://topia.wikidot.com/interlopers-css">here</a> (applied to the tale <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/interlopers">Interlopers</a>). No other CSS themes will go on my pages for the canon until this one is done and is made to be the best it can be.</p> <p>And to address the elephant in the room, a canon hub isn't ready yet. Just a bit more left to do before AAPA can go live.</p> <p><strong>EDIT:</strong> The new theme is live!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
